The approach of discarding perfectly functional silicon every few years is an engineering failure born of lazy design. Instead of treating older hardware as obsolete scrap, the Neo Euclidean Logic Operating System (NELOS) treats legacy machines the exact same way customizers in the 1970s treated classic 1950s car chassis. They didn't dump them in a landfill; they chopped the tops, dropped the suspensions, chromed the engines, and transformed heavy factory steel into high-performance works of art.

